description: Location! - superbly situated & brilliantly designed condo in one of Boston's hippest neighborhoods. Just one block from E Broadway, the home is sited right near all of the action, yet offers a quiet spot to relax - buffered by the Gate of Heaven Church to the south, and a row of brick buildings on the north side of the block. Built in 2011, the building is a neo-colonial style, with a brick exterior & modern & elegant interior - featuring wainscoting, soft lighting & secured entry. The unit is replete with fine details - marble countertops, stainless appliances, recessed lighting & oversized bedrooms - easily accommodating king-sized beds & sizable closets. Main living area is an open-concept with a view of the private patio - ideal for entertaining. Master en-suite tiled bath, tub & in-unit laundry make it convenient. Short stroll to I Street Beach, Castle Island, Medal of Honor Park, American Provisions & numerous top restaurants. Pet friendly, T access & garage parking.
